cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NA. 

The paper deals with the problem of high-dimensional misspecified phase retrieval, which involves signal recovery using sampling vectors and measurements related by an unknown link function. This problem is related to several sub-fields of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures (cs.DS), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Given the focus on signal recovery and the use of sparse PCA, cs.IT and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CV due to the mention of geometric prior information. The use of algorithms and analysis suggests cs.DS and cs.NA as possible sub-categories as well.
